<br>
First, I want them to stun using <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Gnoll Hide Lariats</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->, especially <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Earth</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> pets.  A pet that stuns and roots, oh yeah.<br>
Second, occasionally I want to armor the pet, including the elemental defender, which I would like them to equip on their back, not their secondary slot.  So I give them a pair of <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Dagger of Symbols</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> first, so it equips on their back.<br>
Finally, sometimes I want to give them more save versus magic, in which case I might give them three <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Daggers of Symbol</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->, with the third one going in the ranged slot.<br>
<br>
Rarely do I see summoned mobs, nor have I been satisfied with the performance of either <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Sword of Runes</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> or <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Velium Weapons</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->.  However, stun becomes increasingly important against mobs that cast or hit hard.<br>
