<br>
Honestly, I am not the best person to ask about what is true in the middle levels nowadays, as I have no lower level mage alts.  My best recollection is that 24ish they are still wielding two handers, but by 39ish dual wielding is at least semi-automatic.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Dagger of Symbols</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> has plus 5 versus magic, fire, and cold, so <!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><u>might</u><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END--> be a better choice against casters.  If so, remember you can give a third dagger to go in the range slot.  Again, it also allows for <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Elemental Defender</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> to be worn on the back, so in general, yes, if I am going to do it, I use that spell.<br>
<br>
However, I have been told that <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> piercing</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> weapons have a special <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> &quot;power,&quot;</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> in that they hit the target more often, but less often for max.  I have no idea whether this lowers DPS, but if the enemy has an undispelled damage shield, it does mean the pet will take more damage since it will hit more often.  I do not recall what the special <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> &quot;powers&quot;</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> are for <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> slashing</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> and <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> blunt</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> weapons.<br>
<br>
Farming lariats is <!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><u>good</u><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END-->, because there is so much fine steel down there that you will make decent money as well.  Also, it gives you an excuse to return to <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> South Karana</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> and check on a certain reclusive pegasus.  I have not tried the casters down there post-post-post-patch, but before <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> The Great Patch</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> I would sometimes get charmed, kill my pet, and barely escape with my life at level 60.  MR gear made no difference, they can just charm you because they can.  Try to take on gnolls one at a time, no matter how green you think they are.  Trust me, you will live longer.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Raz</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
